snippet.title: The full injury list: round 20
snippet.content:
The Giants will miss star forward Jeremy Cameron for three weeks

Updated: Tuesday, August 1
Early prognosis
Betts, Crouch and Lever are all chances of facing Port Adelaide on Sunday. Lever has missed the past two games with what the club says is a minor hamstring injury. Hartigan re-injured his hamstring in the first quarter of Adelaide's SANFL game last weekend - his first game back after missing three weeks. - Lee Gaskin

Young Daicos' hopes of making his AFL debut before season's end have taken a hit after he sustained a foot injury in the VFL. More finger surgery means Pendlebury might not be seen again this season, while Varcoe definitely won't play again this year after undergoing elbow surgery. - Ben Collins

Early prognosis
Merrett is set to miss the rest of the season after breaking his leg in last week's VFL win. The speedy wingman/forward hasn't played at senior level this season. Green is expected to be available after missing two weeks with a hamstring injury, while Brown is still touch and go to be available again in 2017. - Callum Twomey

Updated: Thursday, July 27
Early prognosis
Langdon's knee continues to plague him and the youngster could miss another two weeks after twice making short-lived comeback bids since round 10. Pearce and Clarke strode out in run-throughs at training on Tuesday, along with Duman who is a few weeks from a WAFL comeback. Walters has avoided surgery on his injured knee, but will not play again this season. - Travis King

Gibson and Frawley will also likely play again this season, while O'Meara's long-awaited return appears just one week away. - Ashley Browne

Updated: Tuesday, August 1
Early prognosis
Waite will spend a fourth stint for the year on the sidelines, including a third from injury, because of a second calf setback, while Williams and Wright join the long list of players done for the season. Wood will also miss at least a fifth match, after some initial optimism of a swift return. Larkey is a chance to return at AFL or VFL level, while Preuss did not appear on the club's official injury list despite hurting his back at the weekend. - Marc McGowan

Early prognosis
Riewoldt will find out on Thursday morning if he is available to play, with his fate in doctor's hands after having several stitches in his right eye. Prestia should be available after being rested with knee and calf soreness. Morris has been sidelined for five matches with a hamstring injury and is due to push his case for a return, likely through the VFL. - Nathan Schmook

Saints coach Alan Richardson was last week "really hopeful" McCartin would be back this weekend, with not many hurdles left for the forward to jump over. Stevens missed last week with a sore groin but could return. Armitage didn't play in the VFL last week after experiencing groin soreness. Coughlan re-injured his hamstring and faces more time on the sidelines. - Dinny Navaratnam

Updated: Thursday, July 27
Early prognosis
The Eagles have lost star midfielders Priddis and Jetta for Sunday's clash against the Lions, while Lycett still hasn't recovered from his shoulder injury and could be done for the season. Venables' turf toe injury remains an issue. The top draftee was listed as three weeks away last round, but is now indefinite and looks doubtful to return this season. Willie Rioli (hamstring) and Simon Tunbridge (ACL) both got through comeback games unscathed in the WAFL reserves on Saturday. - Travis King
